    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 18</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 2</em>, <em>Advanced Player's Guide pg. 176</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 11 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 11 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> brace, disarm, reach, see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Two-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Martial</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Polearms</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>The blade of this polearm is a curved or hooked chopping blade with a spiked projection on the back of the blade. The spike is commonly used to block and parry. When fighting defensively or with full defense, this weapon gives you a +1 shield bonus to AC. A mounted opponent hit by a bill takes a -1 penalty on his Ride check to stay mounted.</p>",
